comments.text:
Hello Akash and all audiences of Deshbhakt, to the best of my understanding, the issue lies with the Maneuvering Characteristics Augmentation System (MCAS) software installed in certain Boeing aircraft. The horizontal stabilizer, located at the rear of the aircraft, becomes difficult to control manually when the MCAS is activated. I may be mistaken, as I do not come from an aeronautics background, but this is my interpretation of the problem. Similar issues were observed in the Boeing 737 Max crashes involving Lion Air Flight 610 in October 2018 and Ethiopian Airlines Flight 302 in March 2019.

It is also worth noting that the Boeing 787 Dreamliner has faced problems related to its lithium-ion batteries, which have been known to overheat and, in some cases, catch fire. However, this may not be the cause in this case, as there were no reports of smoke or fire.
